<subSubSection pageId="142" pageNumber="143" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="142.[151,1436,1733,2009]" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,466,1805,1830]" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Differential Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Very similar in dorsal habitus and ventral structures to the other member of the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Fenestella</emphasis>
group, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="2011" box="[289,432,1841,1865]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fenestella">
<emphasis box="[289,309,1842,1865]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[325,432,1841,1865]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">fenestella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[448,558,1841,1865]" captionStart="FIGURE 266" captionStartId="344.[151,250,1753,1776]" captionTargetBox="[224,1366,209,1707]" captionTargetId="figure-29@344.[208,1379,193,1732]" captionTargetPageId="344" captionText="FIGURE 266. Hydraena fenestella, holotype, dorsal and lateral habitus, and venter." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5283939" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5283939/files/figure.png" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Figs. 266</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[570,616,1841,1865]" captionStart="FIGURE 267" captionStartId="345.[151,250,1753,1776]" captionTargetBox="[248,1348,215,1713]" captionTargetId="figure-25@345.[223,1364,193,1732]" captionTargetPageId="345" captionText="FIGURE 267. Hydraena herzogestella, holotype, dorsal and lateral habitus, and venter." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5283943" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5283943/files/figure.png" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">267</figureCitation>
); differing therefrom in larger size (ca. 1.32 vs. 
<quantity box="[1164,1266,1841,1865]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.22" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" unit="mm" value="1.22">1.22 mm</quantity>
) and in plaque ratios (ca. 6/1/6/5 vs. 5/1.5/5/4). Reliable determinations will require careful examination of the male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[159,324,1913,1937]" captionStart="FIGURES 268–269" captionStartId="346.[151,264,1564,1587]" captionTargetBox="[261,1338,237,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-32@346.[226,1360,193,1543]" captionTargetPageId="346" captionText="FIGURES 268–269. Aedeagi of holotypes. 268. H. fenestella. 269. H. herzogestella." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5283945" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5283945/files/figure.png" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Figs. 268, 269</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
